(
<emphasis box="[482,609,1955,1977]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="207">R. Shtein 580</emphasis>
). Detail of the flowers and inflorescence. A. Deltoid-tipped buds. B. Flowers at anthesis, grown in full sun, showing the large corolla that dilates in the apical ¾. C. Inflorescences with some wilted flowers and peduncles that become devoid of bracts during anthesis. D–F. Details of a flower and the abaxial leaf blade surface, as well as a corolla, and pistil, respectively—all not to scale, grid segment in each element represents 5 mm. Photographs: Ronen Shtein.
